[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":2148},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":2123,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F08\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur\u002F":2132},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20231008\u002F2016996949\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":2107,"date":2108,"description":26,"extension":2109,"lang":2110,"meta":2111,"navigation":274,"path":2112,"readingMinutes":2113,"seo":2114,"standalone":2115,"stem":2116,"tags":2117,"tldr":2120,"updated":2108,"url":2121,"__hash__":2122},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fday-24-deploying-to-zeabur.md","Day 24 - Deploying to Zeabur","8429141456",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":2099},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,30,33,36,39,55,58,61,69,72,76,79,82,167,191,194,236,239,701,704,989,992,1386,1389,1666,1669,1754,1757,1770,1783,1786,1792,1795,1801,1804,1810,1813,1819,1822,1828,1831,1837,1840,1843,1849,1852,1858,1861,1867,1870,1876,1881,1884,1890,1896,1902,1905,1910,1917,1922,1929,2021,2025,2028,2046,2049,2058,2061,2064,2067,2076,2079,2082,2089,2092,2095],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"Zeabur","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2014.22.48.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"After getting the basic concept of servers in the previous post, of course we have to actually deploy a project to a server.",[20,28,17],{"id":29},"zeabur",[12,31,32],{},"Zeabur is a PaaS platform. What's PaaS? Platform as a Service.",[12,34,35],{},"A bit vague? Let me give an example. Say you want to build a house. What do you need? Foundation, cement, bricks, wood, etc. — not to mention designing the house itself. These are all things you need to do.",[12,37,38],{},"The PaaS concept is like hiring a professional construction company to build it for you. The company provides services like design, construction, materials, etc. — you just tell them what house you want and they build it. That's the PaaS concept.",[12,40,41,42,46,47,50,51,54],{},"So in this concept, you're the ",[43,44,45],"strong",{},"developer",", the construction company is the ",[43,48,49],{},"PaaS platform",", and the house is the ",[43,52,53],{},"project",". You just focus on project development without worrying about server issues — that's the benefit of PaaS.",[12,56,57],{},"There are many common PaaS platforms — for example, Heroku (which became paid earlier) is a PaaS platform. So we don't have to worry too much about server issues — just register an account, create a project, deploy the project. Pretty convenient.",[12,59,60],{},"The core idea of PaaS platforms is abstracting away the complex server management work, so you can focus on project development. Really convenient for beginners.",[62,63,66],"callout",{"title":64,"type":65},"Note","note",[12,67,68],{},"There's also IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service) and SaaS (Software as a Service), but those aren't what we're covering here. Look them up if interested.",[12,70,71],{},"Why am I picking Zeabur? Because Zeabur is a Taiwanese PaaS platform — gotta support local platforms. Plus Zeabur offers a free plan ($5\u002Fmonth), and it's really convenient. So let's use Zeabur to deploy our project.",[20,73,75],{"id":74},"deploying","Deploying",[12,77,78],{},"I'll walk you through deploying the previous post's project to Zeabur step by step. You can also try first and come back if you have issues.",[12,80,81],{},"Below are the corresponding commands and the code we expect to deploy — making sure your code matches mine for smooth deployment:",[83,84,89],"pre",{"className":85,