lass":1685},"sWTrB","  \"name\"",[93,1688,1689],{"class":211},": ",[93,1691,1692],{"class":103},"\"example-discord-crawler\"",[93,1694,334],{"class":211},[93,1696,1697],{"class":95,"line":116},[93,1698,1699],{"class":205},"  \u002F\u002F ... other code omitted\n",[93,1701,1702,1705],{"class":95,"line":128},[93,1703,1704],{"class":1685},"  \"scripts\"",[93,1706,1707],{"class":211},": {\n",[93,1709,1710,1713,1715,1718],{"class":95,"line":137},[93,1711,1712],{"class":1685},"    \"start\"",[93,1714,1689],{"class":211},[93,1716,1717],{"class":103},"\"node index.js\"",[93,1719,334],{"class":211},[93,1721,1722,1725,1727,1730,1734,1737,1739],{"class":95,"line":145},[93,1723,1724],{"class":1685},"    \"test\"",[93,1726,1689],{"class":211},[93,1728,1729],{"class":103},"\"echo ",[93,1731,1733],{"class":1732},"sbsOT","\\\"",[93,1735,1736],{"class":103},"Error: no test specified",[93,1738,1733],{"class":1732},[93,1740,1741],{"class":103}," && exit 1\"\n",[93,1743,1744],{"class":95,"line":153},[93,1745,1498],{"class":211},[93,1747,1748],{"class":95,"line":161},[93,1749,1699],{"class":205},[93,1751,1752],{"class":95,"line":337},[93,1753,965],{"class":211},[12,1755,1756],{},"Now push this project to GitHub Repositories — Zeabur needs your GitHub repo to deploy. I won't elaborate on the GitHub deployment process. Plus Zeabur uses GitHub for sign-up\u002Flogin, so GitHub is required.",[62,1758,1759],{"title":64,"type":65},[12,1760,1761,1762,1769],{},"If first-time using GitHub, see my post ",[1763,1764,1768],"a",{"href":1765,"rel":1766},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fgit\u002F20210709\u002F1381487661\u002F",[1767],"nofollow","Connecting\u002Fuploading to GitHub via SSH (Ed25519) (article in Mandarin)"," and try pushing the project to GitHub.",[12,1771,1772,1773,1776,1777,1779,1780,651],{},"Reminder — don't push ",[90,1774,1775],{},".env"," to GitHub. It contains your Discord Token. If pushed publicly, your Discord Token gets exposed and your Discord Bot can be controlled by others. Always add ",[90,1778,1775],{}," to ",[90,1781,1782],{},".gitignore",[12,1784,1785],{},"Now go to Zeabur. Since Zeabur uses GitHub for sign-up\u002Flogin:",[12,1787,1788],{},[1763,1789,1790],{"href":1790,"rel":1791},"https:\u002F\u002Fdash.zeabur.com\u002Flogin",[1767],[12,1793,1794],{},"You can directly log in with GitHub:",[12,1796,1797],{},[15,1798],{"alt":1799,"src":1800},"GitHub login","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2014.56.20.png",[12,1802,1803],{},"After logging in, you'll go straight to the Zeabur dashboard. Click \"Create Project\":",[12,1805,1806],{},[15,1807],{"alt":1808,"src":1809},"Create project","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2015.00.25.png",[12,1811,1812],{},"Pick the project region — let's pick \"Taiwan\" (FYI: Zeabur servers are in GCP's Taiwan datacenter):",[12,1814,1815],{},[15,1816],{"alt":1817,"src":1818},"Taiwan","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2015.01.11.png",[12,1820,1821],{},"You'll see your newly created project:",[12,1823,1824],{},[15,1825],{"alt":1826,"src":1827},"New Project","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fnew%20Project.png",[12,1829,1830],{},"Click it to see project info. Quick overview:",[12,1832,1833],{},[15,1834],{"alt":1835,"src":1836},"Project intro","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002FZeabur_service_dash.jpg",[12,1838,1839],{},"I won't elaborate on project settings — explore on your own.",[12,1841,1842],{},"Let's deploy our service (project). Click \"Create Service\" and you'll see Git and Marketplace options. Pick Git since we're deploying from GitHub:",[12,1844,1845],{},[15,1846],{"alt":1847,"src":1848},"Git Deploy","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fzeabur_deploy_git.png",[12,1850,1851],{},"Pick the project to deploy:",[12,1853,1854],{},[15,1855],{"alt":1856,"src":1857},"Project","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fzeabur_deploy_git2.jpg",[12,1859,1860],{},"The whole deploy takes about 1-2 minutes:",[12,1862,1863],{},[15,1864],{"alt":1865,"src":1866},"Deploy","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2016.15.07.png",[12,1868,1869],{},"Click \"Log\" to see the deploy process:",[12,1871,1872],{},[15,1873],{"alt":1874,"src":1875},"Log","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2016.31.52.png",[12,1877,1878],{},[15,1879],{"alt":1874,"src":1880},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002FZeabur_log.jpg",[12,1882,1883],{},"You'll likely find Log shows an error:",[12,1885,1886],{},[15,1887],{"alt":1888,"src":1889},"Error","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-09-08%2016.39.27.png",[12,1891,1892,1893,1895],{},"Because we didn't set Env vars. Back at the project dashboard, there's an Environment Variables section at the bottom. Click \"Edit Environment Variables\" and you can paste ",[90,1894,1775],{}," contents directly:",[12,1897,1898],{},[15,1899],{"alt":1900,"src":1901},"Env","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002FZeabur_env.jpg",[12,1903,1904],{},"After saving, click ReDeploy and it'll work normally.",[12,1906,1907],{},[15,1908],{"alt":1909,"src":1875},"ReDeploy",[12,1911,1912,1913,1916],{},"Back to Discord, your Discord Bot should be online. Try ",[90,1914,1915],{},"\u002Fblog"," to test — your Discord Bot should reply with an article.",[1918,1919,1921],"h3",{"id":1920},"about-auto-registering-commands","About auto-registering commands",[12,1923,1924,1925,1928],{},"One more thing — about command registration. We added a file called ",[90,1926,1927],{},"register.js"," for registering commands. To make sure commands are always up-to-date, we can register commands via npm scripts so we don't have to manually register every time:",[83,1930,1932],{"className":1671,"code":1931,"language":1673,"meta":88,"style":88},"{\n  \"name\": \"example-discord-crawler\",\n  \u002F\u002F ... other code omitted\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"postinstall\": \"node register.js\",\n    \"start\": \"node index.js\",\n    \"test\": \"echo \\\"Error: no test specified\\\" && exit 1\",\n    \"register\": \"node register.js\"\n  },\n  \u002F\u002F ... other code omitted\n}\n",[90,1933,1934,1938,1948,1952,1958,1970,1980,1999,2009,2013,2017],{"__ignoreMap":88},[93,1935,1936],{"class":95,"line":96},[93,1937,1680],{"class":211},[93,1939,1940,1942,1944,1946],{"class":95,"line":107},[93,1941,1686],{"class":1685},[93,1943,1689],{"class":211},[93,1945,1692],{"class":103},[93,1947,334],{"class":211},[93,1949,1950],{"class":95,"line":116},[93,1951,1699],{"class":205},[93,1953,1954,1956],{"class":95,"line":128},[93,1955,1704],{"class":1685},[93,1957,1707],{"class":211},[93,1959,1960,1963,1965,1968],{"class":95,"line":137},[93,1961,1962],{"class":1685},"    \"postinstall\"",[93,1964,1689],{"class":211},[93,1966,1967],{"class":103},"\"node register.js\"",[93,1969,334],{"class":211},[93,1971,1972,1974,1976,1978],{"class":95,"line":145},[93,1973,1712],{"class":1685},[93,1975,1689],{"class":211},[93,1977,1717],{"class":103},[93,1979,334],{"class":211},[93,1981,1982,1984,1986,1988,1990,1992,1994,1997],{"class":95,"line":153},[93,1983,1724],{"class":1685},[93,1985,1689],{"class":211},[93,1987,1729],{"class":103},[93,1989,1733],{"class":1732},[93,1991,1736],{"class":103},[93,1993,1733],{"class":1732},[93,1995,1996],{"clas